Rating: 3
This is a great recipe with a few of my modifications......pound the chicken and coat with a pine nut mixture (process pine nuts in a food processor and add only a small amount of flour and salt and pepper) After the pine nut crust is a nice golden brown and chicken is cooked through, transfer to a platter and keep warm in oven. Saute 16oz pkg of mushrooms( white or baby bellas )sliced in half, add the cream, sundried tomatoes and fresh basil ( you must use fresh! - I omit the wine) Let simmer for a few minutes until all flavors combine and sauce thickens, pour over chicken and serve. I usually serve this with a green vegetable and roasted red skinned potatoes.

