Rating: 3
I admit to tinkering with the recipe as follows: after browning the chicken (and putting it in the oven to finish cooking), I sauteed 1/2 cup shallots with 2 teas minced garlic, until softened and just beginning to brown. I increased the wine to 12 oz and let it reduce. Then I added the cream (1 cup?) and let it reduce again with the sun dried tomatoes, and 2 TBL tomato paste (for color and taste). This made enough sauce to coat 8 oz of spinach fettucine and coat the chicken (add the juices that have accumulated). Use the oil from the tomatoes to saute the chicken in for additional flavor, and add grated parmesan at the end if you want the sauce thicker. All in all, it is quick and tasty for when you want something new to do with boneless chiken breasts.

